Nigerian star, Oyinkansola Sarah Aderibigbe, also known as Ayra Starr has recounted her ordeal in the hands of the Nigerian Immigration Service, NIS. The ‘Rush’ crooner on her Twitter handle disclosed that she was forced to remove her eyelash extensions by an Immigration officer or else she would not be attended to. “This passport office people really made me just remove my lashes.” According to the vocalist, “ I’ll never forgive y’all.” The Contonu-born singer, who began her singing career at the age of 16 years was officially signed into Mavin Records in January 2020 after Music Executive, Don Jazzy came across her song titled ‘Damage’ on her Instagram page.